responseText: NSLOCTEXT("", "7BE8E90E4F9D4E71A756CBA1487E8B7D", "Day 24, Goblin Rune Expedition. The runes seem to elude me, yet their existence is surely fact. Far too many eyes have reported seeing the stones within the goblin camps of the Riverlands. This is but another testament to the intelligence of the goblinada species, low as it may be. My fact finding mission has led me to the Aela ruins of all places. Somewhere amidst the ancient rubble of defeat sits a Blood Rune, painted in the medium blood and sacrifice. I\'d pay handsomely for the location of said rune. - Professor Arthur G. Hughes the Third, anthropologist and gobologist specialist to the Arcane Academy.  ")
name: CSQ_DialDef_0004_TBR_ResearchNotes_3
